Description:
We are looking for a results-oriented individual with a strong grasp of the digital landscape to join our Business Intelligence team, and help grow our Digital & Growth Marketing, as well as our Brand & Content teams’ knowledge, through the use of data and analytics. This position is best suited for someone with a passion for sport, but an even larger passion for data and understanding. If you are entering the field of data and analytics and are looking to merge your passions together, then we may have the role for you!
What you’ll do:
Work with various digital tools (email automation, social media platforms, websites) to bring in new customers and convert our followers through the use of data analysis;
Track, report and optimize on our digital tools to create peak efficiencies;
Create customer journeys for segments from our database to nurture patrons through the sales and marketing pipeline;
Help create targeted digital advertisements based on data and sports-based knowledge;
Exchange ideas/data/feedback with other departments (Ticket Sales, Digital Marketing & Growth, Brand & Content) in order to help scale and improve our selling and marketing efforts;
Plan, execute, measure and report on A/B tests and experiments;
Analyze social data and users’ feedback and action off of insights;
Create plans focused on improving our marketing strategy that are based on data;
Be a self-starter with ability to manage multiple projects in a dynamic environment with shifting priorities;
Creative innovative processes and ideas for product offerings and presentation.
What’s Needed:
Post-secondary degree in mathematics, statistics or another scientific related field;
1-2 years of experience in a data focused role, new graduates encouraged to apply;
Intermediary to expert level knowledge of Microsoft Excel and data manipulation is a
must;
Experience with any of the following digital tools considered and asset;
Salesforce
Tableau
Email automation systems (Adobe Campaign, Marketo, etc.)
Ticketing Platforms (Paciolan, Ticketmaster, etc.)
Google Analytics
Survey Monkey
Facebook Ads Manager
A willingness to learn new tools and strategies, with a quick uptake time;
Data-driven, with a clear understanding of data, analytics, metrics and their importance;
A good storyteller: being able to convey your findings in an effective, clear and concise manner for all levels of staff;
Innovative and challenges the status quo;
A desire to go beneath the surface and discover and distill a problem down into a very clear set of hypotheses that can be tested. Wanting to know why data says what it does;
Pro-active and effective in managing projects and their deadlines while considering all stakeholders;
Strong communication skills, both verbally and written with the ability to anticipate needs before they occur.
Why OSEG?
OSEG operates the largest professional multi-sport business in Ottawa, operating the Ottawa REDBLACKS, and Ottawa 67’s, while hosting basketball, soccer, live events, concerts, festivals and year-round community activities.
Our employees are empowered to make sure our customers and fans keep coming back – it is our secret sauce that sets our events and our venue apart. To do that OSEG fosters a culture that values respect, teamwork, hustle and humour. We offer a competitive total rewards package, unique entertainment and fitness perks, an unbeatable location on the canal in the heart of the Glebe and a backstage pass to one of Ottawa’s busiest sports and entertainment hubs.
